cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.CE

The paper deals with power allocation and interference cancellation techniques in wireless communication systems, which are typically studied in the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The use of distributed antenna systems and the joint allocation of subcarriers, antennas, and power also suggest a Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of multiple antennas for multi-user MIMO (cs.MM) and the consideration of complexity in the design of the techniques, which could fall under Computer Engineering (cs.CE).
